of <em>Arcane</em> season 2</a> was a heartbreak we saw coming; too many things lined up just right between the disappearance of Powder and Vi\u2019s father figure and the creation of the horrifying werewolf creature to be a coincidence. What we might ", "id": 1536393, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tv/479484/arcane-netflix-league-legends-warwick-vander-viktor", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Warwick is the perfect example of what makes Arcane\u2019s animation so special", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-18T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Against a pink background with a trophy, Varl, Clementine, Koromaru, Lae\u2019zel, and Garrus appear in a collage for the Video Game Companion Hall of Fame\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Graphic: Matt Patches/Polygon | Source images: Various\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/compnaionHOF.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Not every story is meant to be experienced alone. Sometimes, the protagonist needs a friend or a foil, and having companion characters is a great way to achieve that. That\u2019s why we took the time to look back on the vast collection of gaming companions from over the years, and narrowed the selection down to a rare few. This is the first class of Polygon\u2019s Video Game Companion Hall of Fame, an illustrious honor for the best pals in the medium.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-al", "id": 1535864, "language": null, "link": "http